/* ============================================================================
 * 12-0 — Game config (static, hand-authored)
 * Pure data, no logic. Loaded as a classic script (globals below).
 *
 *   STEPS         — the 3 "how it works" cards on the home screen
 *   SETUPS        — the 4 team shapes (formations); each locks 5 role slots
 *   SWISS_STAGES  — the three Swiss stages of a Major (base opponent strengths)
 *   PLAYOFFS      — the single-elimination playoff rounds
 *
 * The draftable squads (SQUADS) and opponent names (OPP_POOL) live in
 * src/squads.js, which is generated by scripts/build-data.js.
 *
 * Player object (in squads.js): { n: nickname, c: country, r: era HLTV-style
 *   rating, awp: is an AWPer, roles: [functional role tags] }
 *   Optional provenance fields from the pipeline: src (source tag/url),
 *   est (true when the rating is estimated), and a squad-level lowConfidence.
 *   The engine ignores these extra fields.
 * Squads are unique per (team, year). reroll keys on the exact team name.
 * Role tags: awp | igl | entry | support | lurker | rifle | star
 * ==========================================================================*/

